node.title: Stunning images of longest partial lunar eclipse in centuries
node.description: The longest partial lunar eclipse in nearly 600 years was visible on Friday.
node.content: ["The longest partial lunar eclipse in centuries was visible overnight across all of North America and parts of South America.", "In this photo, the Earth's shadow covers the full moon during a partial lunar eclipse visible near a statue of George Washington atop Baltimore's Washington Monument, on Friday, November 19, 2021, in Baltimore, Maryland.\u00a0"]
